                <h1>Rajasthan Free Tractor & Krishi Yantra Yojana Eligibility Criteria</h1>
                <h3>DESCRIPTION:</h3>
                <p>Free Tractor and Krishi Yantra Yojana has been launched by the Chief Minister of the state, Ashok Gehlot Ji, to provide
                benefits to the small and marginal farmers of the state under this scheme. From the free side, facilities of tractor and
                agricultural machinery will be provided in the fields for harvesting, threshing and other agricultural activities. If
                any farmer wants to avail the benefit of Rajasthan Free Tractor Yojana 2021, you can contact Jfarm Services by sending
                an SMS to 9282222885 number, calling this number or sms any device Can order for All Eligible Applicants who want to
                apply to this scheme.</p>

                <h3>Eligibility criteria:</h3>
                <p>• The applicant should be a permanent resident of Rajasthan state.<br>
                • Under this scheme, economically weaker small and marginal farmers of the state will be eligible.<br>
                • Farmers of the state should have cultivable land.<br>
                • It is necessary for the applicant to have agricultural land in his own name / in the case of undivided family, the
                name of the applicant in the revenue record.<br>
                • In order to get the grant for a tractor powered agricultural machine, the tractor must be registered in the name of
                the applicant.<br>
                </p>

                <h3>Benefits of the Scheme:</h3>
                <p>• Economically weaker small and marginal farmers can contact Jfarm Services by sending an SMS on 9282222885 to avail
                this scheme for free rent.<br>
                • On the demand from eligible farmers, service is being provided through the company’s registered tractors and
                threshers.<br>
                • About 5 lakh trucks and 20 thousand tractors are connected in it, which will take the products of the farmers like
                grains, pulses, vegetables, fruits etc. to the mandis, railway stations, airports, etc. at competitive rates.<br>
                • A farmer will be given a grant only once in a three-year period on any type of agricultural machine (eg seed-less
                fertilizer drill, plow, thresher, etc.) in any scheme of the department. A farmer can be given a grant on a maximum of 3
                different types of agricultural implements in all the schemes in a financial year.<br>

                </p>
                <h3>Documents require to get benefit of the scheme:</h3>
                <p>1. Applicant should have his Ration card (Bhamashah Card)<br>
                    2. Applicant should have at least 6 months old Jamabandi.<br>
                    3. Affidavit of land.<br>
                    4. Updated Aadhar card<br>
                    5. Passport Size photographs.<br>
        
                </p>
